This paper deals with the use of Bregman divergences in machine learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of projections and norm-enforcing algorithms, which could fall under "Information Theory" (cs.IT) or "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses clustering on curved manifolds, which could be categorized under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) or "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
